HEADWORD: Phono-
<hw>Pho"no-</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A combining form from Gr.
<grk>fwnh`</grk> <sig>sound</sig>, <sig>tone</sig>; <as>as,
<ex>phono</ex>graph, <ex>phono</ex>logy</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phono</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Phono
<hw>Phono</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
South American butterfly (<spn>Ithonia phono</spn>) having nearly
transparent wings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phonocamptic</ent>⟦br⟧
